OL,3,CSuper soil: How a farmer makes money
OL,4,Cfrom storing carbon underground
OL,6,FPlants absorb carbon dioxide from the
OL,7,Fatmosphere through photosynthesis, and
OL,8,Fit transfers to the soil through a
OL,9,Fplant's roots. Soil organisms feed on
OL,10,Fthese roots, locking carbon
OL,11,Funderground.
OL,13,FBut unhealthy soil releases the carbon
OL,14,Fback into the atmosphere - especially
OL,15,Fif it has been ploughed, or left bare
OL,16,Fand dry. Whereas, if healthy soil is
OL,17,Fcovered by grass, plants or cover
OL,18,Fcrops, it's almost impossible for the
OL,19,Fcarbon to escape.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/11
