OL,3,CSuper soil: How a farmer makes money
OL,4,Cfrom storing carbon underground
OL,6,FTypical farms often have bare soil
OL,7,Fwhen crops are not in season or the
OL,8,Fland has been ploughed, but on
OL,9,FHylton's farm it's pretty much always
OL,10,Fa sea of green.
OL,12,FOn expansive fields of wheat and
OL,13,Fbarley crops, Hylton grows a cover
OL,14,Fcrop like clover underneath - so that
OL,15,Fthere is coverage all year round.
OL,17,FIt ensures the carbon is locked into
OL,18,Fthe soil "where it belongs".
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/11
